# Git push & deploy (Cursor)

User deploys via **GitHub Actions** on push to `origin`. Prefer doing git from Cursor terminal — do not ask user to open IntelliJ.

## When to run git

- **Push:** ONLY when the user explicitly says so (e.g. "push et", "deploy et", "GitHub'a gönder"). Never push because a plan/todo says so — always ask first: "Push edim?" unless the user already said push in that message.
- **Commit:** ONLY when the user explicitly asks to commit. Do not commit proactively after implementing a feature.
- Never commit/push proactively after code changes alone.

## Tests

- Do **not** add unit/integration tests unless the user explicitly asks for tests.

## Standard push flow

1. `git status` + `git diff` — review what will ship
2. Stage only relevant files (never `.env`, secrets, credentials)
3. Commit with a short message focused on **why**
4. `git push origin HEAD` (branch is usually `main`)
5. Report commit hash and confirm push succeeded

## Remote

- `origin`: https://github.com/azizJava91/carcat-service.git
- Default branch: `main`

## If push fails

- Auth: user may need GitHub PAT (HTTPS) or SSH key configured once on this machine
- Never `git push --force` to `main` unless user explicitly requests it
